00:24:50.560 --> 00:24:52.460

        BUT THE LINE THAT SANG OF


00:24:52.460 --> 00:24:55.190

        "MY NEIGHBORS BLACK AND WHITE"
        WAS CUT FROM THE FILM.
      

00:24:55.190 --> 00:24:57.260

        SO LONG, MEN.


00:24:57.260 --> 00:25:02.630

        BYE.
        BYE.
      

00:25:02.630 --> 00:25:05.370

        Narrator: EUROPEAN IMMIGRANTS
        WERE LEARNING THAT WHITENESS
      

00:25:05.370 --> 00:25:07.400

        WAS MORE THAN SKIN COLOR,


00:25:07.400 --> 00:25:08.710

        IT WAS THE PRIVILEGE


00:25:08.710 --> 00:25:12.480

        OF OPPORTUNITY,
        AND ABOVE ALL, EXCLUSIVE.
      

00:25:12.480 --> 00:25:15.180

        Goodman: THERE'S THIS WHOLE
        VERY STANDARD NARRATIVE
      

00:25:15.180 --> 00:25:18.080

        OF THE EUROPEAN MOBILITY MODEL.


00:25:18.080 --> 00:25:21.320

        WE CAME HERE WITH NOTHING,
        WE WORKED HARD,
      

00:25:21.320 --> 00:25:23.120

        WE PULLED OURSELVES UP
        BY OUR BOOTSTRAPS.
      

00:25:23.120 --> 00:25:24.920

        AND IT'S OFFERED UP AS PROOF


00:25:24.920 --> 00:25:30.830

        OF THE OPENNESS
        OF THE AMERICAN ECONOMIC ORDER.
      

00:25:30.830 --> 00:25:32.900

        Narrator:
        LEFT OUT OF THE BOOTSTRAP MYTH
      

00:25:32.900 --> 00:25:34.670

        OF EUROPEAN ETHNICS


00:25:34.670 --> 00:25:40.840

        WAS ACCESS TO OPPORTUNITIES
        CLOSED TO NON-WHITES.
      

00:25:40.840 --> 00:25:43.810

        ROOSEVELT'S NEW DEAL REFORMS
        OFFERED MANY AMERICANS
      

00:25:43.810 --> 00:25:47.080

        A PATH OUT OF POVERTY.


00:25:47.080 --> 00:25:49.580

        Roosevelt:
        THIS SOCIAL SECURITY MEASURE
      

00:25:49.580 --> 00:25:52.780

        GIVES AT LEAST SOME PROTECTION


00:25:52.780 --> 00:25:55.950

        TO 50 MILLIONS OF OUR CITIZENS.


00:25:55.950 --> 00:25:58.990

        Narrator: BUT THE ORIGINAL
        SOCIAL SECURITY PROGRAM
      

00:25:58.990 --> 00:26:02.130

        EXCLUDED FARM WORKERS
        AND DOMESTICS,
      

00:26:02.130 --> 00:26:05.800

        MOST OF WHOM WERE NON-WHITE.


00:26:05.800 --> 00:26:08.160

        AND MANY UNIONS
        LOCKED BLACKS AND MEXICANS
      

00:26:08.160 --> 00:26:09.970

        INTO LOW-PAYING JOBS,


00:26:09.970 --> 00:26:13.300

        OR KEPT THEM OUT ALTOGETHER.


00:26:13.300 --> 00:26:16.740

        BUT PERHAPS THE BEST EXAMPLE
        OF HOW EUROPEAN ETHNICS
      

00:26:16.740 --> 00:26:19.810

        WOULD FINALLY GAIN
        THE FULL BENEFITS OF WHITENESS
      

00:26:19.810 --> 00:26:21.980

        CAME WITH
        AN INNOVATION IN HOUSING
      

00:26:21.980 --> 00:26:32.820

        AT THE END OF WORLD WAR II.


00:26:32.820 --> 00:26:35.360

        IT WAS A TIME WHEN
        HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS
      

00:26:35.360 --> 00:26:38.160

        OF G.I.s CAME HOME,
        READY TO START FAMILIES,
      

00:26:38.160 --> 00:26:44.500

        BUT HAD NO PLACE TO LIVE.


00:26:44.500 --> 00:26:48.470

        Man:
        LIVING SPACE WAS AT A PREMIUM.
      

00:26:48.470 --> 00:26:50.270

        IN THE BRONX THEY TRIED


00:26:50.270 --> 00:26:52.980

        BUILDING QUONSET HUTS,


00:26:52.980 --> 00:26:54.240

        AND THEY TURNED TO SLUMS,


00:26:54.240 --> 00:26:56.910

        ALL THE QUONSET HUTS
        JUST DISINTEGRATED.
      

00:26:56.910 --> 00:26:59.350

        THERE WERE TWO FAMILIES
        SHARING A HUT.
      

00:26:59.350 --> 00:27:01.620

        ONE FAMILY AT ONE END,
        ONE FAMILY AT THE OTHER,
      

00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:04.860

        AND BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,
        THEY WERE AWFUL.
      

00:27:04.860 --> 00:27:06.820

        Announcer:
        FHA CAME TO THE RESCUE
      

00:27:06.820 --> 00:27:08.790

        BY ENSURING LONG-TERM


00:27:08.790 --> 00:27:10.660

        LOW MONTHLY PAYMENT
        MORTGAGE LOANS.
      

00:27:10.660 --> 00:27:13.960

        Narrator: VETERANS
        NEEDED HOMES FOR FAMILIES.
      

00:27:13.960 --> 00:27:15.370

        THEY TURNED TO


00:27:15.370 --> 00:27:17.470

        A REVOLUTIONARY
        NEW DEAL HOUSING PROGRAM.
      

00:27:17.470 --> 00:27:20.540

        IT WOULD RACIALIZE
        HOUSING WEALTH AND OPPORTUNITY
      

00:27:20.540 --> 00:27:24.310

        FOR DECADES IN WAYS
        FEW COULD HAVE IMAGINED.
      

00:27:24.310 --> 00:27:28.050

        Oliver: IN THE 1930s,
        THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT CREATED
      

00:27:28.050 --> 00:27:30.650

        THE FEDERAL HOUSING
        ADMINISTRATION,
      

00:27:30.650 --> 00:27:34.480

        WHOSE JOB IT WAS
        TO PROVIDE LOANS,
      

00:27:34.480 --> 00:27:36.550

        OR THE BACKING FOR LOANS,


00:27:36.550 --> 00:27:40.360

        TO AVERAGE AMERICANS,
        SO THEY COULD PURCHASE A HOME.
      

00:27:40.360 --> 00:27:42.390

        Announcer:
        DUE TO THE STIMULATION
      

00:27:42.390 --> 00:27:43.860

        OF THE NATIONAL HOUSING ACT,


00:27:43.860 --> 00:27:46.900

        FROM EVERY SECTION OF
        THE COUNTRY COME REPORTS OF --
      

00:27:46.900 --> 00:27:49.700

        Oliver: IN ORDER
        TO PURCHASE A HOUSE IN AMERICA
      

00:27:49.700 --> 00:27:51.640

        PRIOR TO THE 1930s,


00:27:51.640 --> 00:27:54.840

        YOU HAD TO PAY 50%
        OF THE SALES PRICE
      

00:27:54.840 --> 00:27:58.180

        UP FRONT.


00:27:58.180 --> 00:28:01.210

        THE NEW TERMS
        OF PURCHASING A HOME
      

00:28:01.210 --> 00:28:04.950

        WAS THAT YOU PUT
        10% OR 20% DOWN
      

00:28:04.950 --> 00:28:08.890

        AND THE BANK FINANCED 80% OF IT,


00:28:08.890 --> 00:28:11.720

        NOT OVER FIVE YEARS,
        BUT OVER 30 YEARS,
      

00:28:11.720 --> 00:28:16.960

        AT RELATIVELY LOW RATES.


00:28:16.960 --> 00:28:19.130

        THIS OPENED UP THE OPPORTUNITIES


00:28:19.130 --> 00:28:21.800

        FOR AMERICANS TO OWN HOMES
        LIKE NEVER BEFORE.
      

00:28:21.800 --> 00:28:27.340

        THE AVERAGE PERSON
        COULD OWN THAT HOME.
      

00:28:27.340 --> 00:28:29.410

        Narrator:
        IF THESE TERMS SOUND FAMILIAR,
      

00:28:29.410 --> 00:28:32.340

        THEY SHOULD,
        BECAUSE THIS IS ESSENTIALLY
      

00:28:32.340 --> 00:28:34.150

        THE SAME FINANCING SCHEME


00:28:34.150 --> 00:28:38.080

        THAT ALLOWS MOST AMERICANS
        TO OWN THEIR HOMES TODAY.
      

00:28:38.080 --> 00:28:40.950

        FEDERAL PROGRAMS AND BANKS


00:28:40.950 --> 00:28:43.990

        SANK MILLIONS INTO
        THE HOME CONSTRUCTION INDUSTRY.
      

00:28:43.990 --> 00:28:46.460

        THEIR MESSAGE TO VETERANS --


00:28:46.460 --> 00:28:49.630

        YOU CAN AFFORD A NEW HOME,


00:28:49.630 --> 00:28:57.270

        BUY A NEW HOME NOW.


00:28:57.270 --> 00:29:00.370

        ON THE OUTSKIRTS
        OF BALTIMORE, MEMPHIS,
      

00:29:00.370 --> 00:29:03.780

        CHICAGO, LOS ANGELES, DENVER,


00:29:03.780 --> 00:29:05.780

        AND OTHER CITIES,


00:29:05.780 --> 00:29:10.610

        BRAND-NEW COMMUNITIES SPRANG UP.


00:29:10.610 --> 00:29:15.020

        ONE OF THE MOST FAMOUS WAS
        A LONG ISLAND POTATO FIELD,
      

00:29:15.020 --> 00:29:19.060

        TRANSFORMED INTO
        17,000 NEW HOMES.
      

00:29:19.060 --> 00:29:22.760

        IT WAS CALLED LEVITTOWN.


00:29:22.760 --> 00:29:25.630

        TAX DOLLARS HELPED MAKE
        THE SINGLE FAMILY HOME
      

00:29:25.630 --> 00:29:28.800

        A MASS-PRODUCED CONSUMER ITEM.


00:29:28.800 --> 00:29:30.830

        THE AMERICAN DREAM
        HAD A NEW NAME --
      

00:29:30.830 --> 00:29:35.940

        SUBURBIA.


00:29:35.940 --> 00:29:37.380

        Juliano: YOU HAVE TO REMEMBER,


00:29:37.380 --> 00:29:39.080

        THE PEOPLE WHO CAME HERE


00:29:39.080 --> 00:29:42.150

        IN 1947, 1948,


00:29:42.150 --> 00:29:47.320

        WERE YOUNG EX-G.I.s
        WHOSE UPPERMOST CONCERN WAS
      

00:29:47.320 --> 00:29:49.320

        TAKING ADVANTAGE
        OF THE G.I. BILL
      

00:29:49.320 --> 00:29:52.660

        AND MAKING THINGS BETTER
        FOR THEMSELVES.
      

00:29:52.660 --> 00:29:54.490

        Narrator:
        BEFORE MOVING TO LEVITTOWN,
      

00:29:54.490 --> 00:29:56.830

        HERB KALISMAN AND HIS WIFE DORIS


00:29:56.830 --> 00:30:00.700

        LIVED IN A CRAMPED ATTIC
        APARTMENT IN NEW YORK CITY.
      

00:30:00.700 --> 00:30:03.670

        Doris: AND WHEN WE BEGAN
        TO LOOK FOR AN APARTMENT
      

00:30:03.670 --> 00:30:07.340

        WE FOUND THAT THE APARTMENTS
        WERE 100, 125,
      

00:30:07.340 --> 00:30:10.040

        $150 A MONTH.


00:30:10.040 --> 00:30:12.010

        I KNOW
        THAT'S UNBELIEVABLE TODAY,
      

00:30:12.010 --> 00:30:14.680

        BUT IT WAS
        TOO EXPENSIVE FOR US.
      

00:30:14.680 --> 00:30:17.680

        AND OUT HERE IN LEVITTOWN,


00:30:17.680 --> 00:30:21.420

        THE MORTGAGE PAYMENTS
        WERE $65 A MONTH.
      

00:30:21.420 --> 00:30:22.890

        [ TELEPHONE RINGING ]


00:30:22.890 --> 00:30:26.020

        THEY SAY YOUR KITCHEN
        DAZZLES EVERY EYE.
      

00:30:26.020 --> 00:30:28.860

        ♪ A BRAND-NEW SINK,
        A BUILT-IN OVEN ♪
      

00:30:28.860 --> 00:30:31.360

        ♪ A NEW REFRIGERATOR
        AND A PHONE ♪
      

00:30:31.360 --> 00:30:33.260

        Juliano: IF YOU WERE BUYING
        A LEVITT HOME
      

00:30:33.260 --> 00:30:36.030

        IN 1947, '48,


00:30:36.030 --> 00:30:38.700

        '49, '50, AND '51,


00:30:38.700 --> 00:30:40.370

        YOU WOULD GET --


00:30:40.370 --> 00:30:41.470

        THIS WOULD BE YOUR KITCHEN.


00:30:41.470 --> 00:30:44.610

        YOU WOULD GET A G.E. STOVE,


00:30:44.610 --> 00:30:48.380

        G.E. REFRIGERATOR,
        AND A BENDIX WASH MACHINE.
      

00:30:48.380 --> 00:30:55.050

        IT WOULD BE PART
        OF THE REAL ESTATE.
      

00:30:55.050 --> 00:30:57.490

        Man: WE CAME TO
        LEVITTOWN AND WE
      

00:30:57.490 --> 00:31:00.160

        FOUND A MODEL HOUSE


00:31:00.160 --> 00:31:04.660

        AND WE WALKED IN
        AND WE LOOKED AROUND.
      

00:31:04.660 --> 00:31:09.330

        AND, OF COURSE,
        IN THE EYES OF A YOUNG MAN
      

00:31:09.330 --> 00:31:12.670

        WHO WAS RAISED IN THE GHETTO,
        SO TO SPEAK,
      

00:31:12.670 --> 00:31:14.740

        IT WAS AN
        INTERESTING EXPERIENCE,
      

00:31:14.740 --> 00:31:18.940

        AN INTERESTING LIFESTYLE,
        SEEING ALL THE NEW
      

00:31:18.940 --> 00:31:20.850

        MODERN CONVENIENCES.


00:31:20.850 --> 00:31:24.250

        VERY FASCINATING.


00:31:24.250 --> 00:31:26.850

        Narrator:
        EUGENE BURNETT CAME HOME
      

00:31:26.850 --> 00:31:29.690

        WITH ALMOST A MILLION
        OTHER BLACK G.I.s.
      

00:31:29.690 --> 00:31:32.190

        THEY HAD FOUGHT FOR THE COUNTRY


00:31:32.190 --> 00:31:34.190

        IN SEGREGATED RANKS.


00:31:34.190 --> 00:31:36.530

        THEY RETURNED
        HOPING FOR EQUALITY
      

00:31:36.530 --> 00:31:38.660

        AND THE AMERICAN DREAM.


00:31:38.660 --> 00:31:41.700

        FOR MANY,
        THAT DREAM WAS A NEW HOME
      

00:31:41.700 --> 00:31:43.530

        FOR LITTLE MONEY DOWN,


00:31:43.530 --> 00:31:47.700

        AND SOME OF THE EASIEST
        CREDIT TERMS IN HISTORY.
      

00:31:47.700 --> 00:31:49.940

        Eugene:
        I WENT UP TO THE SALESMAN.
      

00:31:49.940 --> 00:31:52.040

        WE'RE INTERESTED
        IN YOUR HOME,
      

00:31:52.040 --> 00:31:53.880

        WE'RE INTERESTED IN
        BUYING ONE
      

00:31:53.880 --> 00:31:55.510

        AND WHAT
        IS THE PROCEDURE?
      

00:31:55.510 --> 00:31:58.880

        IS THERE AN APPLICATION
        TO BE FILLED OUT?
      

00:31:58.880 --> 00:32:02.150

        SO HE LOOKED AT ME,


00:32:02.150 --> 00:32:04.250

        LOOKED AROUND,


00:32:04.250 --> 00:32:05.460

        AND HE SAID TO ME, HE SAYS,


00:32:05.460 --> 00:32:07.220

        LISTEN, IT'S NOT ME,


00:32:07.220 --> 00:32:10.330

        BUT THE OWNERS OF THIS
        DEVELOPMENT HAVE NOT,
      

00:32:10.330 --> 00:32:12.160

        AS YET, DECIDED


00:32:12.160 --> 00:32:16.270

        TO SELL THESE HOMES
        TO NEGROES.
      

00:32:16.270 --> 00:32:18.500

        Bernice:
        IT WAS AS THOUGH IT WASN'T REAL.
      

00:32:18.500 --> 00:32:20.340

        YOU CAN'T IMAGINE,


00:32:20.340 --> 00:32:25.940

        FOR SOMEONE TO COME OUT
        AND ACTUALLY TELL YOU THAT
      

00:32:25.940 --> 00:32:27.440

        THEY CAN'T SELL TO YOU,
        YOU KNOW?
      

00:32:27.440 --> 00:32:29.180

        I WAS REALLY ON A --


00:32:29.180 --> 00:32:32.850

        OH, MAN, LOOK AT THIS HOUSE,
        CAN YOU IMAGINE HAVING THIS?
      

00:32:32.850 --> 00:32:34.520

        AND THEN FOR THEM TO TELL ME


00:32:34.520 --> 00:32:40.190

        BECAUSE OF THE COLOR OF MY SKIN
        I CAN'T BE A PART OF IT?
      

00:32:40.190 --> 00:32:43.490

        Narrator:
        THE FHA UNDERWRITERS WARNED
      

00:32:43.490 --> 00:32:47.100

        THAT THE PRESENCE OF EVEN ONE
        OR TWO NON-WHITE FAMILIES
      

00:32:47.100 --> 00:32:49.370

        COULD UNDERMINE
        REAL ESTATE VALUES
      

00:32:49.370 --> 00:32:53.200

        IN THE NEW SUBURBS.


00:32:53.200 --> 00:32:55.710

        THESE GOVERNMENT GUIDELINES
        WERE WIDELY ADOPTED
      

00:32:55.710 --> 00:33:00.980

        BY PRIVATE INDUSTRY.


00:33:00.980 --> 00:33:03.180

        RACE HAD LONG PLAYED A ROLE


00:33:03.180 --> 00:33:07.650

        IN LOCAL REAL ESTATE PRACTICES.


00:33:07.650 --> 00:33:09.890

        STARTING IN THE 1930s,


00:33:09.890 --> 00:33:12.320

        GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS
        INSTITUTIONALIZED
      

00:33:12.320 --> 00:33:14.460

        A NATIONAL APPRAISAL SYSTEM


00:33:14.460 --> 00:33:18.160

        WHERE RACE WAS AS MUCH A FACTOR
        IN REAL ESTATE ASSESSMENT
      

00:33:18.160 --> 00:33:21.500

        AS THE CONDITION
        OF THE PROPERTY.
      

00:33:21.500 --> 00:33:23.170

        USING THIS SCHEME,


00:33:23.170 --> 00:33:25.740

        FEDERAL INVESTIGATORS EVALUATED


00:33:25.740 --> 00:33:28.670

        239 CITIES ACROSS THE COUNTRY


00:33:28.670 --> 00:33:32.010

        FOR FINANCIAL RISK.


00:33:32.010 --> 00:33:34.310

        Oliver: SO THAT THOSE
        COMMUNITIES THAT WERE ALL-WHITE,
      

00:33:34.310 --> 00:33:36.680

        SUBURBAN, AND FAR AWAY


00:33:36.680 --> 00:33:38.520

        FROM MINORITY AREAS,


00:33:38.520 --> 00:33:40.680

        THEY RECEIVED
        THE HIGHEST RATING,
      

00:33:40.680 --> 00:33:44.990

        AND THAT WAS THE COLOR GREEN.


00:33:44.990 --> 00:33:47.520

        THOSE COMMUNITIES
        THAT WERE ALL MINORITY
      

00:33:47.520 --> 00:33:49.090

        OR IN THE PROCESS OF CHANGING,


00:33:49.090 --> 00:33:54.030

        THEY GOT THE LOWEST RATING...


00:33:54.030 --> 00:33:59.200

        AND THE COLOR RED,
        THEY WERE RED-LINED.
      

00:33:59.200 --> 00:34:00.800

        AS A CONSEQUENCE,


00:34:00.800 --> 00:34:04.640

        MOST OF THE MORTGAGES
        WENT TO SUBURBANIZING AMERICA,
      

00:34:04.640 --> 00:34:08.650

        AND IT SUBURBANIZED IT RACIALLY.


00:34:08.650 --> 00:34:10.710

        Goodman: THE RACIAL LOGIC


00:34:10.710 --> 00:34:15.280

        ADOPTS THE PRINCIPLE THAT
        AN INTEGRATED NEIGHBORHOOD
      

00:34:15.280 --> 00:34:18.160

        IS A BAD RISK,
        IS A FINANCIAL RISK --
      

00:34:18.160 --> 00:34:19.660

        THAT AN INTEGRATED NEIGHBORHOOD


00:34:19.660 --> 00:34:22.320

        IS LIKELY TO BE
        AN UNSTABLE NEIGHBORHOOD.
      

00:34:22.320 --> 00:34:24.830

        UNSTABLE SOCIALLY, BUT THEREFORE


00:34:24.830 --> 00:34:28.670

        ALSO UNSTABLE ECONOMICALLY.


00:34:28.670 --> 00:34:30.170

        Narrator:
        WHEN THE WHITE RESIDENTS
      

00:34:30.170 --> 00:34:31.930

        OF EIGHT MILE ROAD IN DETROIT


00:34:31.930 --> 00:34:34.470

        WERE TOLD THEY WERE TOO CLOSE
        TO A BLACK NEIGHBORHOOD
      

00:34:34.470 --> 00:34:38.010

        TO QUALIFY
        FOR A POSITIVE FHA RATING,
      

00:34:38.010 --> 00:34:39.840

        THEY BUILT THIS SIX-FOOT WALL


00:34:39.840 --> 00:34:43.350

        BETWEEN THEMSELVES
        AND THEIR BLACK NEIGHBORS.
      

00:34:43.350 --> 00:34:45.180

        ONCE THE WALL WENT UP,


00:34:45.180 --> 00:34:50.090

        MORTGAGES ON THE WHITE
        PROPERTIES WERE APPROVED.
      

00:34:50.090 --> 00:34:53.520

        BETWEEN 1934 AND 1962,


00:34:53.520 --> 00:34:55.190

        THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT
        UNDERWROTE
      

00:34:55.190 --> 00:34:59.700

        $120 BILLION IN NEW HOUSING.


00:34:59.700 --> 00:35:04.970

        LESS THAN 2% WENT TO NON-WHITES.


00:35:04.970 --> 00:35:07.140

        Bernice:
        I CAN UNDERSTAND AN INDIVIDUAL
      

00:35:07.140 --> 00:35:11.140

        DEPENDING ON HIS ENVIRONMENT
        OR HIS FAMILY OR WHATEVER
      

00:35:11.140 --> 00:35:12.810

        BEING RACIST,


00:35:12.810 --> 00:35:16.810

        BUT FOR YOUR COUNTRY
        TO SANCTION IT,
      

00:35:16.810 --> 00:35:20.320

        GIVE HIM TOOLS TO DO THAT,


00:35:20.320 --> 00:35:27.490

        THERE'S SOMETHING
        DEFINITELY WRONG THERE.
      

00:35:27.490 --> 00:35:29.490

        Herb Kalisman: I THINK WE HAD
        THE GOLDEN CHANCE
      

00:35:29.490 --> 00:35:32.300

        AFTER WORLD WAR II
        AND WE FLUBBED IT.
      

00:35:32.300 --> 00:35:38.170

        BECAUSE HERE WE HAD
        A G.I. BILL THAT WAS,
      

00:35:38.170 --> 00:35:41.670

        YOU KNOW,
        THAT WAS AVAILABLE TO EVERYBODY,
      

00:35:41.670 --> 00:35:45.680

        BUT IN A WAY THEY DIDN'T
        MAKE IT AVAILABLE TO EVERYBODY.
      

00:35:45.680 --> 00:35:47.680

        AND THAT WAS
        A GOLDEN OPPORTUNITY
      

00:35:47.680 --> 00:35:49.680

        IN THIS COUNTRY
        AND WE MISSED IT,
      

00:35:49.680 --> 00:35:54.490

        WE REALLY MISSED IT.


00:35:54.490 --> 00:35:56.520

        Man: BUT YOU CAN ALWAYS TELL,
        CAN'T YOU?
      

00:35:56.520 --> 00:35:58.550

        A TOWN WITH GOOD
        REAL ESTATE PEOPLE
      

00:35:58.550 --> 00:36:01.490

        IS A MORE
        SUBSTANTIAL COMMUNITY,
      

00:36:01.490 --> 00:36:03.630

        BECAUSE MORE PEOPLE
        OWN THEIR OWN HOMES.
      

00:36:03.630 --> 00:36:05.090

        THAT'S RIGHT.


00:36:05.090 --> 00:36:07.530

        Man: AND NOW IT'S
        SORT OF HARD TO BELIEVE
      

00:36:07.530 --> 00:36:09.970

        THAT THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT
        NATIONALIZED
      

00:36:09.970 --> 00:36:11.770

        AND INTRODUCED RED LINING.


00:36:11.770 --> 00:36:15.610

        IN A FUNNY WAY, IT WASN'T
        JUST GIVING SOMETHING TO WHITES,
      

00:36:15.610 --> 00:36:18.740

        IT WAS CONSTRUCTING WHITENESS.


00:36:18.740 --> 00:36:21.450

        WHITENESS MEANT, AS IN THE PAST,


00:36:21.450 --> 00:36:24.380

        WHITE HAD MEANT BEING A CITIZEN
        AND BEING A CHRISTIAN.
      

00:36:24.380 --> 00:36:25.720

        IT NOW MEANT


00:36:25.720 --> 00:36:30.990

        LIVING IN THE SUBURBS.


00:36:30.990 --> 00:36:32.990

        Narrator: ONLY 50 YEARS BEFORE,


00:36:32.990 --> 00:36:36.430

        EUROPEAN ETHNICS WERE BELIEVED
        TO BE DISTINCT RACES.
      

00:36:36.430 --> 00:36:38.660

        NOW, IN THESE NEW
        SEGREGATED NEIGHBORHOODS,
      

00:36:38.660 --> 00:36:42.330

        THEY BLENDED TOGETHER
        AS WHITE AMERICANS.
      

00:36:42.330 --> 00:36:48.010

        Doris Kalisman: WE DID HAVE
        DIFFERENT RELIGIOUS GROUPS,
      

00:36:48.010 --> 00:36:49.610

        WE WERE MIXED UP THERE,


00:36:49.610 --> 00:36:53.510

        BUT WE WERE
        AN ALL-WHITE COMMUNITY,
      

00:36:53.510 --> 00:36:57.950

        AND I THINK
        IT'S AN UNREALISTIC WORLD.
      

00:36:57.950 --> 00:37:00.250

        I THINK THERE'S
        SOMETHING STERILE
      

00:37:00.250 --> 00:37:03.890

        ABOUT EVERYONE BEING
        ON THE SAME ECONOMIC LEVEL
      

00:37:03.890 --> 00:37:09.890

        AND EVERYONE
        BEING THE SAME COLOR.
      

00:37:09.890 --> 00:37:12.200

        Man:
        IT CERTAINLY DOESN'T PROMOTE
      

00:37:12.200 --> 00:37:16.130

        A FEELING OF A WIDER WORLD --


00:37:16.130 --> 00:37:18.840

        WIDER, NOT WHITER --


00:37:18.840 --> 00:37:20.370

        TO LIVE IN A PLACE


00:37:20.370 --> 00:37:21.970

        WHERE THERE ARE ONLY PEOPLE
        THAT LOOK LIKE YOU.
      

00:37:21.970 --> 00:37:25.470

        Narrator:
        CARTOONIST BILL GRIFFITH
      

00:37:25.470 --> 00:37:29.350

        REMEMBERS MOVING FROM BROOKLYN
        TO LEVITTOWN AS A KID.
      

00:37:29.350 --> 00:37:32.520

        Griffith: IT'S AN UNTENABLE,
        ARTIFICIAL WORLD.
      

00:37:32.520 --> 00:37:34.020

        YOU'RE CREATING


00:37:34.020 --> 00:37:36.250

        A WEIRD UTOPIA IN A WAY,


00:37:36.250 --> 00:37:39.020

        A UTOPIA OF,


00:37:39.020 --> 00:37:42.330

        YOU KNOW,
        MIDDLE-CLASS WHITE PEOPLE
      

00:37:42.330 --> 00:37:43.990

        WHO WERE TRYING TO DENY
        THAT THEY WERE LIVING
      

00:37:43.990 --> 00:37:45.660

        IN A MULTI-RACIAL WORLD.


00:37:45.660 --> 00:37:47.330

        AND HOW LONG
        CAN YOU KEEP THAT UP?
      

00:37:47.330 --> 00:37:55.770

        YOU CAN'T KEEP THAT UP FOREVER.


00:37:55.770 --> 00:37:57.010

        WHETHER THERE WERE


00:37:57.010 --> 00:37:59.340

        GOING TO BE BLACK PEOPLE
        IN LEVITTOWN, WAS JUST --
      

00:37:59.340 --> 00:38:00.840

        IT WOULD BE
        ALMOST THE EQUIVALENT OF SAYING
      

00:38:00.840 --> 00:38:05.280

        ARE THERE GOING TO BE
        MARTIANS IN LEVITTOWN?
      

00:38:05.280 --> 00:38:08.550

        Powell: THE BASIC IDEA OF
        WHITENESS IS WHO'S INCLUDED,
      

00:38:08.550 --> 00:38:10.120

        WHO'S PART OF THE FAMILY,


00:38:10.120 --> 00:38:16.730

        AND IT HAS
        MATERIAL CONSEQUENCES.
      

00:38:16.730 --> 00:38:19.460

        BLACKS WEREN'T COMPLETELY
        LEFT OUT OF THE HOUSING MARKET.
      

00:38:19.460 --> 00:38:21.860

        THE HOUSING MARKET
        THAT THEY WERE EXPOSED TO
      

00:38:21.860 --> 00:38:23.630

        WAS LARGELY PUBLIC HOUSING.


00:38:23.630 --> 00:38:26.400

        AND PUBLIC HOUSING,
        FIRST OF ALL, WAS BUILT
      

00:38:26.400 --> 00:38:29.470

        ALMOST EXCLUSIVELY,
        WITH A FEW EXCEPTIONS,
      

00:38:29.470 --> 00:38:34.010

        IN THE CENTRAL CITY.


00:38:34.010 --> 00:38:37.150

        AND AFTER WORLD WAR II
        WE STARTED BUILDING
      

00:38:37.150 --> 00:38:40.150

        LARGER AND LARGER
        PUBLIC HOUSING PROJECTS,
      

00:38:40.150 --> 00:38:46.090

        WHICH WERE CALLED
        VERTICAL GHETTOS.
      

00:38:46.090 --> 00:38:48.490

        ALL OF A SUDDEN
        YOU WERE CONCENTRATING
      

00:38:48.490 --> 00:38:54.500

        LARGE NUMBERS OF POOR PEOPLE
        OF COLOR IN ONE PLACE.
      

00:38:54.500 --> 00:38:57.430

        Narrator:
        ANOTHER FEDERAL PROGRAM,
      

00:38:57.430 --> 00:38:59.100

        URBAN RENEWAL,


00:38:59.100 --> 00:39:05.840

        WAS SUPPOSED TO MAKE CITIES
        MORE LIVABLE.
      

00:39:05.840 --> 00:39:09.280

        90% OF ALL HOUSING
        DESTROYED BY URBAN RENEWAL
      

00:39:09.280 --> 00:39:11.720

        WAS NOT REPLACED.


00:39:11.720 --> 00:39:21.720

        TWO-THIRDS OF THOSE DISPLACED
        WERE BLACK OR LATINO.
      

00:39:21.720 --> 00:39:24.560

        Lyndon Johnson:
        FAIR HOUSING FOR ALL,
      

00:39:24.560 --> 00:39:26.960

        ALL HUMAN BEINGS


00:39:26.960 --> 00:39:30.800

        WHO LIVE IN THIS COUNTRY


00:39:30.800 --> 00:39:35.670

        IS NOW A PART
        OF THE AMERICAN WAY OF LIFE.
      

00:39:35.670 --> 00:39:38.810

        Narrator:
        IN 1968, PRESIDENT JOHNSON
      

00:39:38.810 --> 00:39:40.310

        SIGNED THE FAIR HOUSING ACT.


00:39:40.310 --> 00:39:41.840

        FOR THE FIRST TIME,


00:39:41.840 --> 00:39:44.850

        RACIAL LANGUAGE WAS REMOVED
        FROM FEDERAL HOUSING POLICY.
      

00:39:44.850 --> 00:39:47.720

        NON-WHITE FAMILIES BEGAN MOVING


00:39:47.720 --> 00:39:57.960

        INTO TRADITIONALLY
        WHITE COMMUNITIES IN NUMBERS.
      

00:39:57.960 --> 00:39:59.660

        Woman: WE LIVED IN AN APARTMENT,


00:39:59.660 --> 00:40:02.670

        A TWO-FAMILY HOUSE IN QUEENS.


00:40:02.670 --> 00:40:04.330

        AND WHEN WE CAME HERE


00:40:04.330 --> 00:40:06.000

        IT WAS THE FIRST TIME
        WE HAD BOUGHT A HOUSE.
      

00:40:06.000 --> 00:40:11.170

        AND I WAS LOOKING FOR EVERYTHING
        IN THE STORYBOOKS.
      

00:40:11.170 --> 00:40:12.840

        Narrator:
        THE FRISBYS MOVED FROM QUEENS
      

00:40:12.840 --> 00:40:14.610

        TO SUBURBAN ROOSEVELT,


00:40:14.610 --> 00:40:18.680

        ONLY A FEW MILES
        FROM LEVITTOWN.
      

00:40:18.680 --> 00:40:20.250

        LIKE THE FRISBYS,


00:40:20.250 --> 00:40:22.520

        MANY NON-WHITE FAMILIES
        WOULD DISCOVER
      

00:40:22.520 --> 00:40:28.520

        THE ECONOMIC VALUE OF RACE
        IN THE REAL ESTATE MARKET.
      

00:40:28.520 --> 00:40:32.030

        THEY WATCHED AS THEIR HOMES
        AND NEIGHBORHOODS IN SUBURBIA
      

00:40:32.030 --> 00:40:41.910

        DECLINED PRECISELY BECAUSE
        THEY HAD MOVED INTO THEM.
      

00:40:41.910 --> 00:40:44.740

        Frisby: WHEN I MOVED
        INTO A NEIGHBORHOOD,
      

00:40:44.740 --> 00:40:48.710

        I THOUGHT IT WOULD STAY INTACT
        THE WAY IT WAS.
      

00:40:48.710 --> 00:40:50.380

        ON THE STREET THAT I MOVED ON


00:40:50.380 --> 00:40:51.880

        WHEN I MOVED THERE,


00:40:51.880 --> 00:40:57.950

        IT WAS PREDOMINATELY WHITE.


00:40:57.950 --> 00:41:03.690

        WITHIN TWO YEARS
        IT WAS PREDOMINATELY BLACK.
      

00:41:03.690 --> 00:41:06.660

        Narrator:
        IT WAS CALLED BLOCKBUSTING.
      

00:41:06.660 --> 00:41:08.500

        REAL ESTATE AGENTS PREYED


00:41:08.500 --> 00:41:11.170

        ON THE RACIAL FEARS
        OF WHITE HOMEOWNERS,
      

00:41:11.170 --> 00:41:13.340

        TO GET THEM
        TO SELL THEIR HOMES QUICKLY
      

00:41:13.340 --> 00:41:16.170

        FOR LESS THAN MARKET VALUE.


00:41:16.170 --> 00:41:18.840

        THE HOMES WERE RESOLD
        TO NON-WHITES
      

00:41:18.840 --> 00:41:21.680

        AT INFLATED PRICES.


00:41:21.680 --> 00:41:23.450

        Woman:
        WELL, THEY WOULD SAY,
      

00:41:23.450 --> 00:41:26.180

        YOU KNOW, WE'RE HAVING
        BLACK PEOPLE MOVE IN.
      

00:41:26.180 --> 00:41:30.190

        NOW, I WILL GIVE YOU CASH IF
        YOU WANT TO SELL ME YOUR HOUSE.
      

00:41:30.190 --> 00:41:33.520

        DO YOU WANT TO STAY WITH
        BLACK PEOPLE NEXT DOOR TO YOU?
      

00:41:33.520 --> 00:41:35.860

        AND THAT'S THE WAY IT WENT ON.


00:41:35.860 --> 00:41:39.260

        AND AS BUNNY SAID,
        A LOT OF THE PEOPLE
      

00:41:39.260 --> 00:41:46.200

        JUST SAID YES,
        I'LL TAKE THE MONEY AND RUN.
      

00:41:46.200 --> 00:41:54.210

        AND THAT'S THE START
        OF THE WHITE PEOPLE LEAVING.
      

00:41:54.210 --> 00:41:55.810

        Narrator: AS MORE
        BLACK AND LATINO FAMILIES
      

00:41:55.810 --> 00:41:57.580

        MOVED TO ROOSEVELT,


00:41:57.580 --> 00:42:00.350

        REAL ESTATE BECAME
        MORE AND MORE DEPRESSED,
      

00:42:00.350 --> 00:42:03.650

        JUST AS THE FHA HAD PREDICTED.


00:42:03.650 --> 00:42:05.660

        BUT WHY?


00:42:05.660 --> 00:42:08.320

        Man: I HAVE AN IDEA MY HOUSE
        IS PROBABLY WORTH AROUND
      

00:42:08.320 --> 00:42:12.830

        120 IN THIS TOWN.


00:42:12.830 --> 00:42:16.500

        BUT IT WOULD BE WORTH
        IN MONTOUR
      

00:42:16.500 --> 00:42:20.940

        OR GARDEN CITY
        OR SOME OTHER PLACE...
      

00:42:20.940 --> 00:42:24.040

        PROBABLY AROUND
        200,000 OR BETTER.
      

00:42:24.040 --> 00:42:28.680

        NOW YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT 80,000.


00:42:28.680 --> 00:42:31.480

        YOU SAID TO ME ONE TIME


00:42:31.480 --> 00:42:33.850

        ABOUT WHY DO PEOPLE


00:42:33.850 --> 00:42:37.020

        DISLIKE THE BLACKS?


00:42:37.020 --> 00:42:41.860

        WELL, MONEY-WISE,
        THERE'S A REASON.
      

00:42:41.860 --> 00:42:45.030

        NOT THAT YOU DISLIKE
        THE BLACKS SO MUCH,
      

00:42:45.030 --> 00:42:49.700

        BUT YOU DISLIKE WHAT HAPPENS


00:42:49.700 --> 00:42:54.540

        WHEN A COMMUNITY TURNS
        FROM WHITE TO BLACK.
      

00:42:54.540 --> 00:42:57.210

        Narrator: IT WASN'T
        AFRICAN-AMERICANS MOVING IN
      

00:42:57.210 --> 00:42:59.980

        THAT CAUSED HOUSING VALUES
        TO GO DOWN IN ROOSEVELT
      

00:42:59.980 --> 00:43:01.980

        AND OTHER NEIGHBORHOODS,


00:43:01.980 --> 00:43:04.110

        IT WAS WHITES LEAVING.


00:43:04.110 --> 00:43:05.580

        Man: WHEN A NEIGHBORHOOD,


00:43:05.580 --> 00:43:08.120

        A PREVIOUSLY WHITE NEIGHBORHOOD
        STARTS TO INTEGRATE,
      

00:43:08.120 --> 00:43:11.360

        EVEN IF INDIVIDUAL WHITES
        DON'T HAVE PERSONAL
      

00:43:11.360 --> 00:43:14.420

        OR PSYCHOLOGICAL ANIMOSITY
        AND RACIAL HATRED,
      

00:43:14.420 --> 00:43:17.290

        THEY STILL HAVE
        AN ECONOMIC INCENTIVE TO LEAVE.
      

00:43:17.290 --> 00:43:19.660

        BECAUSE THEY RECOGNIZE
        THAT OTHERS
      

00:43:19.660 --> 00:43:22.670

        MIGHT MAKE THE SAME CALCULATION
        AND LEAVE FIRST.
      

00:43:22.670 --> 00:43:25.600

        SO YOU GET A VICIOUS CIRCLE


00:43:25.600 --> 00:43:27.500

        WHERE WHITES CALCULATE THAT
        OTHER WHITES ARE GOING TO SELL
      

00:43:27.500 --> 00:43:28.940

        WHEN THE NEIGHBORHOOD
        INTEGRATES,
      

00:43:28.940 --> 00:43:32.180

        THEREFORE THEY WANT TO
        SELL FIRST TO AVOID LOSSES,
      

00:43:32.180 --> 00:43:35.340

        AND THEY ACTUALLY
        MAKE IT HAPPEN,
      

00:43:35.340 --> 00:43:36.880

        THEY MAKE WHITE FLIGHT HAPPEN.


00:43:36.880 --> 00:43:38.850

        AND IF YOU THINK ABOUT
        AFRICAN AMERICANS,
      

00:43:38.850 --> 00:43:41.280

        IF AFRICAN AMERICANS
        ARE 20% OF THAT MARKET,
      

00:43:41.280 --> 00:43:43.450

        IT MEANS THAT 80% OF THE PEOPLE


00:43:43.450 --> 00:43:46.520

        ARE NOT LOOKING
        IN THOSE PLACES FOR HOMES.
      

00:43:46.520 --> 00:43:50.190

        SO THE PRICES OF THOSE HOMES
        DECLINES OR STAYS STABLE.
      

00:43:50.190 --> 00:43:52.360

        AND BANKS CONTRIBUTE TO THIS


00:43:52.360 --> 00:43:56.030

        BY CONTINUALLY MAKING LOANS


00:43:56.030 --> 00:43:59.840

        IN REGIONS
        THAT ARE ON THE RISE,
      

00:43:59.840 --> 00:44:01.400

        WHITE COMMUNITIES,


00:44:01.400 --> 00:44:04.870

        AND MAKING IT DIFFICULT TO
        GET LOANS IN BLACK COMMUNITIES.
      

00:44:04.870 --> 00:44:06.810

        SO THERE'S A DIFFERENCE,
        THERE'S A LACK OF SYMMETRY
      

00:44:06.810 --> 00:44:08.480

        THAT'S IMPORTANT
        TO KEEP IN MIND.
      

00:44:08.480 --> 00:44:11.980

        SO IT'S NOT THE SAME
        WHEN WHITES ARE BY THEMSELVES.
      

00:44:11.980 --> 00:44:13.480

        BECAUSE WHEN THEY ARE
        BY THEMSELVES,
      

00:44:13.480 --> 00:44:16.320

        THEY'RE TAKING
        ALL THE RESOURCES WITH THEM.
      

00:44:16.320 --> 00:44:18.650

        THEY'RE TAKING ALL
        THE AMENITIES WITH THEM.
      

00:44:18.650 --> 00:44:20.520

        BUT WHEN BLACKS
        ARE BY THEMSELVES,
      

00:44:20.520 --> 00:44:22.490

        THEY CAN'T GET LOANS,


00:44:22.490 --> 00:44:24.660

        THEY DON'T HAVE
        A DECENT TAX BASE,
      

00:44:24.660 --> 00:44:25.960

        THERE ARE NO JOBS.


00:44:25.960 --> 00:44:31.500

        AND THEN THAT BECOMES ASSOCIATED
        WITH BLACK SPACE.
      

00:44:31.500 --> 00:44:33.100

        Narrator: IN THE END,


00:44:33.100 --> 00:44:36.510

        WHAT HAPPENED TO ROOSEVELT
        HAPPENS IN MANY NEIGHBORHOODS
      

00:44:36.510 --> 00:44:40.510

        WHEN WHITE FAMILIES
        AND BUSINESSES FLEE.
      

00:44:40.510 --> 00:44:42.850

        THE TAX BASE ERODED.


00:44:42.850 --> 00:44:47.180

        SCHOOLS AND SERVICES DECLINED.


00:44:47.180 --> 00:44:49.690

        THE TOWN WAS SEEN
        BY COUNTY OFFICIALS
      

00:44:49.690 --> 00:44:56.690

        AS A LEGITIMATE DUMPING GROUND
        FOR WELFARE FAMILIES.
      

00:44:56.690 --> 00:44:59.800

        Powell: AT ONE POINT
        WE HAD EXPLICIT LAWS
      

00:44:59.800 --> 00:45:04.930

        THAT SAYS WHITES ARE ON TOP
        AND BLACKS ARE ON THE BOTTOM.
      

00:45:04.930 --> 00:45:07.140

        TODAY WE HAVE
        MANY OF THE SAME PRACTICES
      

00:45:07.140 --> 00:45:10.510

        WITHOUT THE EXPLICIT LANGUAGE.


00:45:10.510 --> 00:45:14.410

        AND THOSE PRACTICES ARE LARGELY
        INSCRIBED IN GEOGRAPHY.
      

00:45:14.410 --> 00:45:19.980

        AND SO GEOGRAPHY DOES THE WORK
        OF JIM CROW LAWS.
      

00:45:19.980 --> 00:45:21.820

        SO, MANY PEOPLE ARE CONFUSED,


00:45:21.820 --> 00:45:23.990

        AS WHY AFTER 50 YEARS
        OF CIVIL RIGHTS
      

00:45:23.990 --> 00:45:25.990

        ARE OUR SCHOOLS
        STILL SEGREGATED,
      

00:45:25.990 --> 00:45:27.990

        WHY ARE HOUSING
        MARKETS STILL SEGREGATED,
      

00:45:27.990 --> 00:45:29.660

        WHY ARE OUR JOBS
        STILL SEGREGATED?
      

00:45:29.660 --> 00:45:32.430

        AND AGAIN, A LOT OF THIS
        IS A FUNCTION OF
      

00:45:32.430 --> 00:45:35.730

        HOW WE'VE RE-INSCRIBED


00:45:35.730 --> 00:45:37.730

        THE RACIAL GEOGRAPHIC SPACE
        IN THE UNITED STATES.
      

00:45:37.730 --> 00:45:41.070

        THAT STRUCTURE IS STILL


00:45:41.070 --> 00:45:48.610

        WHAT WE'RE LIVING WITH TODAY.


00:45:48.610 --> 00:45:52.050

        Narrator:
        AS HOMES IN WHITE COMMUNITIES
      

00:45:52.050 --> 00:45:53.520

        APPRECIATED IN VALUE,


00:45:53.520 --> 00:45:59.120

        THE NET WORTH
        OF THESE WHITE FAMILIES GREW.
      

00:45:59.120 --> 00:46:00.960

        FOR MOST NON-WHITE FAMILIES


00:46:00.960 --> 00:46:02.960

        WHO STAYED
        IN URBAN NEIGHBORHOODS,
      

00:46:02.960 --> 00:46:06.630

        THE HOUSING MARKET OPEN TO THEM
        IN THE '50s AND '60s
      

00:46:06.630 --> 00:46:09.630

        WAS LARGELY A RENTAL MARKET.


00:46:09.630 --> 00:46:16.200

        YOU DON'T GAIN EQUITY
        BY PAYING RENT.
      

00:46:16.200 --> 00:46:18.740

        Conley: WHERE ONE'S FAMILY
        LIVES IN AMERICA
      

00:46:18.740 --> 00:46:22.240

        IS NOT JUST A MATTER
        OF TASTE AND PREFERENCE.
      

00:46:22.240 --> 00:46:24.980

        YOU HAVE THE ISSUE
        OF HOUSING AND WEALTH.
      

00:46:24.980 --> 00:46:27.480

        THE MAJORITY OF AMERICANS


00:46:27.480 --> 00:46:30.020

        HOLD MOST OF THEIR WEALTH
        IN THE FORM OF HOME EQUITY.
      

00:46:30.020 --> 00:46:32.490

        SO, THAT'S THEIR NEST EGG,


00:46:32.490 --> 00:46:34.660

        THAT'S HOW THEY CAN FINANCE


00:46:34.660 --> 00:46:37.990

        THE EDUCATION
        OF THEIR OFFSPRING.
      

00:46:37.990 --> 00:46:41.500

        THAT'S HOW THEY CAN
        SORT OF SAVE UP FOR RETIREMENT.
      

00:46:41.500 --> 00:46:44.170

        IT'S THEIR SAVINGS BANK, RIGHT,


00:46:44.170 --> 00:46:46.840

        THEY'RE LIVING
        IN THEIR SAVINGS BANK.
      

00:46:46.840 --> 00:46:49.010

        Powell: MY FAMILY,
        LIKE A LOT OF FAMILIES,
      

00:46:49.010 --> 00:46:51.540

        WAS IN DETROIT,
        STRUGGLING TO BUY A HOUSE.
      

00:46:51.540 --> 00:46:54.840

        YOU HAD A DUAL HOUSING MARKET,
        ONE WHITE, ONE BLACK.
      

00:46:54.840 --> 00:46:57.010

        A HOUSING MARKET WITH ONE
        WITH A LOT OF DEMAND,
      

00:46:57.010 --> 00:47:00.780

        ANOTHER HOUSING MARKET
        WITH VERY LITTLE DEMAND.
      

00:47:00.780 --> 00:47:03.120

        MY FATHER LIVES IN THE HOUSE
        THAT I GREW UP IN.
      

00:47:03.120 --> 00:47:05.960

        THAT HOUSE TODAY,
        FIVE-BEDROOM HOUSE,
      

00:47:05.960 --> 00:47:07.520

        IS WORTH ABOUT $20,000.


00:47:07.520 --> 00:47:09.960

        THAT SAME HOUSE
        BOUGHT IN THE SUBURBS
      

00:47:09.960 --> 00:47:13.630

        WOULD BE WORTH TODAY
        ABOUT $320,000.
      

00:47:13.630 --> 00:47:15.800

        SO WHITES MOVING TO THE SUBURB


00:47:15.800 --> 00:47:18.640

        WERE BEING SUBSIDIZED
        IN THE ACCUMULATION OF WEALTH,
      

00:47:18.640 --> 00:47:20.500

        WHILE BLACKS
        WERE BEING DIVESTED.
      

00:47:20.500 --> 00:47:23.640

        AND THESE WERE
        PUBLIC POLICY DECISIONS
      

00:47:23.640 --> 00:47:25.810

        IN WHICH ON ONE HAND


00:47:25.810 --> 00:47:29.150

        PEOPLE WERE GIVEN ACCESS
        TO PROPERTY,
      

00:47:29.150 --> 00:47:31.150

        GIVEN TITLE,


00:47:31.150 --> 00:47:33.320

        AND SUBSEQUENTLY, WEALTH,


00:47:33.320 --> 00:47:34.980

        AND ON ANOTHER HAND,


00:47:34.980 --> 00:47:37.650

        WHERE PEOPLE WERE
        NOT GIVEN ACCESS TO PROPERTY,
      

00:47:37.650 --> 00:47:39.320

        DID NOT GENERATE WEALTH,


00:47:39.320 --> 00:47:41.660

        AND DID NOT GENERATE
        THE KIND OF OPPORTUNITY
      

00:47:41.660 --> 00:47:43.230

        FOR THE NEXT GENERATION.


00:47:43.230 --> 00:47:45.830

        SO IF YOU CAN GET
